The paper deals with the engineering of collective adaptive systems, which involves the coordination of multiple devices and the specification of their collective behavior. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of Multiagent Systems (cs.MA). Additionally, the paper proposes a formal foundation for field computations, which involves the use of higher-order calculus and typing, denotational, and operational semantics. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Programming Languages (cs.PL), and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO).
